<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mongkolsamrit, Noisripoom, Thanakitpipattana, Spatafora &amp; Luangsa-ard" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Samsoniella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Samsoniella inthanonensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="inthanonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Samsoniella inthanonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. aurantia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aurantia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. aurantia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having smaller, fusiform to ovoid conidia and a host in the family 
<taxonomicName family="Vespidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Vespidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
